		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Admins can always "delete" images upon request from a user. Anything "deleted" on MediaWiki is hidden from anyone who's not an admin. Most large wikis have one or more pages devoted to deletion requests.
<br />
<br />Think of it this way: What prevents the idiots from uuencoding child porn and posting it to a (text) page?

		

		</td>
